In the realm of copyright and creativity—oh, how we dance on the tightropes strung by laws and regulations! My venture into using Charles Schultz’s creations on a book cover was less about artistic rebellion and more an inquiry into the maze of intellectual property. Who knew Snoopy could be so litigious?

Let's not forget the digital landscape, where I'm crafting tools on Pico XYZ, creating web apps that perhaps might one day replace me at this podium.
